Hello, this is 6 Minute English from BBC Learning English. I'm Phil.

3
00:00:13,000 --> 00:00:19,100
And I'm Pippa. Have you ever phoned up a company and had your call held in a queue?

4
00:00:19,100 --> 00:00:23,000
If you have, then you've probably heard messages like this.

5
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:28,600
Hello, your call is important to us. You are number 89 in the queue.

6
00:00:28,600 --> 00:00:33,600
If you'd like to continue to hold press 1, if you'd like to return to the main menu press 0,

7
00:00:33,600 --> 00:00:37,600
how do you feel when your phone call is put on hold, Phil?

8
00:00:37,600 --> 00:00:40,600
Ah, frustrated usually.

9
00:00:40,600 --> 00:00:45,600
Although I do like it when there's a number saying how many people are in front of you.

10
00:00:45,600 --> 00:00:50,600
Well, when your call is finally connected, it's usually a call centre worker you'll speak to,

11
00:00:50,600 --> 00:00:54,600
a real live person who'll hopefully fix your problem.

12
00:00:54,600 --> 00:01:00,600
But increasingly, this work is now done using artificial intelligence or AI.

13
00:01:00,600 --> 00:01:04,599
And this is causing problems in countries like India and the Philippines,

14
00:01:04,599 --> 00:01:08,599
where call centre jobs make up a big part of the economy.

15
00:01:08,599 --> 00:01:15,599
In this programme, we'll be asking who's really in charge at the call centre? Humans or AI?

16
00:01:15,599 --> 00:01:19,599
